watch & summary 5 points - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SmE4OwHztCc&ab_channel=JSConf
1. Parsing Html document into DOM (Document object model) and parsing css style document into CSSOM (Cascading style sheet object model).
2. DOM tree contains html elements and CSSOM tree contains style elements. This process is called render tree.
3. Layout compute nodes position and size from render tree which will be display on screen.
4. Paint produce bitmap for each layer into texture composite.
5. Further paint compute composite to display on browser screen.
